== Roasted Veggies ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Halve,
peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you
have 1 TBSP.

Toss carrots and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Cooking Oil{4%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While veggies roast, dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. For a
smoother texture, peel potatoes first. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted
water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Pork Chops ==

While potatoes cook, pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @Rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until
you have 2 tsp.

== Rosemary Demi-Glace Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in #pan used for pork{} over medium heat. Add minced onion
and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @Chicken Demi-Glace{1} and @water{¼%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until
slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

== Finishing ==

Return #pot{} with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}
and @Butter{1%tbsp}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes
of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork between plates along with potatoes and veggies. Top pork with sauce
and serve.